}}</ref> In Hahnemann's time, it was reasonable to assume the remedies could be diluted indefinitely, as the concept of the atom or molecule as the [[Avogadro constant|smallest possible unit of a chemical substance]] was just beginning to be recognized. 
The greatest dilution reasonably likely to contain even one molecule of the original substance is 12C.

[[File:Arnica montana homéopathie zoom.jpg|thumb|This bottle contains [[arnica montana]] (wolf's bane) D6, i.e. the nominal dilution is one [[parts per million|part in a million]] (10<sup>'''-6'''</sup>).]]
